# KB-7 Complete Synchronization Architecture: Dual-Stream Implementation

## Executive Summary

This document provides the complete implementation of the dual-stream synchronization architecture, addressing the critical distinction between real-time patient data flow and near-real-time knowledge synchronization, with full details on the Adapter Layer, CDC implementation, and insight distribution patterns.

## 1. Dual-Stream Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Stream 1: Patient Data (Real-Time)"
        EHR[EHR Events] --> |sub-second| Harmonizer
        Harmonizer --> |<100ms| Kafka1[Patient Events Kafka]
        Kafka1 --> |<500ms| Flink[Stream Processing]
    end
    
    subgraph "Stream 2: Knowledge Sync (Near-Real-Time)"
        KB7[KB-7 Terminology] --> |CDC| Debezium
        KB4[KB-4 Safety Rules] --> |CDC| Debezium
        KB2[KB-2 Clinical Context] --> |CDC| Debezium
        Debezium --> |<1min| KafkaChanges[KB Changes Topic]
        KafkaChanges --> |<2min| Adapter[Adapter Service]
        Adapter --> |<2min| Neo4j[Semantic Mesh]
        Adapter --> |<1min| Redis[Cache Layer]
    end
    
    Flink --> |enrichment| Neo4j
    Flink --> |lookups| Redis
    Flink --> |insights| KafkaInsights[Insights Topic]
    
    KafkaInsights --> FHIR[FHIR Store]
    KafkaInsights --> ES[Elasticsearch]
    KafkaInsights --> Push[Push Notifications]
```

